<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1370,1863]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1550,1575]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bertsch" authorityYear="1977" box="[323,468,1550,1575]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Mexichromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[323,468,1550,1575]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Mexichromis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. is externally similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Crosse, 1872)" authorityName="Crosse" authorityYear="1872" baseAuthorityName="Crosse" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[780,1070,1551,1575]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Mexichromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mariei">
<emphasis box="[780,892,1551,1574]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">M. mariei</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Crosse" box="[908,1062,1551,1575]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" refString="Crosse, J. C. H. (1872) Diagnoses molluscorum Novae Caledoniae incolarum. Journal de Conchyliologie, 20, 69 - 74." type="journal article" year="1872">Crosse, 1872</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Based on external morphology, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rudman" box="[151,344,1586,1611]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" refString="Rudman, W. B. (1999 a) Mexichromis cf. mariei. Sea Slug Forum, Australian Museum, Sydney. Available from: http: // www. seaslugforum. net / factsheet / mexicfma (accessed 10 December 2016)" type="journal article" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">Rudman (1999a)</bibRefCitation>
was unsure if this species was 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Crosse" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[719,834,1588,1611]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Mexichromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mariei">
<emphasis box="[719,834,1588,1611]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">M. mariei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or a different species because of inconsistencies in colour pattern between 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Crosse" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[414,524,1623,1646]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Mexichromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mariei">
<emphasis box="[414,524,1623,1646]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">M. mariei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Pacific and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Crosse" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[766,912,1622,1647]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Mexichromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mariei">
<emphasis box="[766,789,1623,1646]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">M</emphasis>
. cf. 
<emphasis box="[839,912,1623,1646]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">mariei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the western Indian Ocean. Therefore, we examined the radula of one specimen and confirmed Rudman’s (1999a) belief that this species is different from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Crosse" baseAuthorityYear="1872" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Mexichromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mariei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">M. mariei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. While the radula formula for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Crosse" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[569,680,1695,1718]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Mexichromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mariei">
<emphasis box="[569,680,1695,1718]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">M. mariei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<date box="[714,754,1694,1719]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" value="1955-10">55x</date>
27.0.27 (+3) (
<bibRefCitation author="Rudman" box="[910,1073,1694,1719]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" refString="Rudman, W. B. (1983) The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia: Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: Chromodoris splendida, C. aspersa and Hypselodoris placida colour groups. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 78, 105 - 173. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1983. tb 00864. x" type="journal article" year="1983">Rudman 1983</bibRefCitation>
), in the specimen examined it is 
<date box="[151,193,1730,1755]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" value="1922-10">22x</date>
15.0.15 (+3) (
<figureCitation box="[347,458,1730,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE12" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1110,1132]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1088]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,195,1088]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE12. RadulaMexichromis sp.(MB28-004850), SEMs of radula.A, General view of the radula.B, Left outermost teeth from the anterior part.C, Innermost teeth.D, Central right lateral and outermost teeth." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1069195/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 12 A</figureCitation>
). Moreover, the very long lateral teeth clearly distinguish these species. The cusp of the lateral tooth is round and the number of denticles varies from two to four (
<figureCitation box="[1005,1116,1766,1791]" captionStart="FIGURE12" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1110,1132]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1088]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,195,1088]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE12. RadulaMexichromis sp.(MB28-004850), SEMs of radula.A, General view of the radula.B, Left outermost teeth from the anterior part.C, Innermost teeth.D, Central right lateral and outermost teeth." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1069195/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 12 B</figureCitation>
). The innermost tooth has a wider base and four denticles on the outer side; these denticles gradually reduce in size from the cusp to the base (
<figureCitation box="[159,304,1838,1863]" captionStart="FIGURE12" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1110,1132]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1088]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,195,1088]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE12. RadulaMexichromis sp.(MB28-004850), SEMs of radula.A, General view of the radula.B, Left outermost teeth from the anterior part.C, Innermost teeth.D, Central right lateral and outermost teeth." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1069195/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 12 C–D</figureCitation>
). In the inner side of the innermost teeth there are one or two denticles (
<figureCitation box="[1109,1218,1838,1863]" captionStart="FIGURE12" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1110,1132]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1088]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,195,1088]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE12. RadulaMexichromis sp.(MB28-004850), SEMs of radula.A, General view of the radula.B, Left outermost teeth from the anterior part.C, Innermost teeth.D, Central right lateral and outermost teeth." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1069195/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 12 C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
